ULAN BATOR, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia reported 161 new COVID-19 infections over the past 24 hours, bringing the national tally to 467,362, the country's health ministry said Wednesday. The nationwide death toll from COVID-19 remains at 2,104 as no deaths were reported, the ministry said. So far, 66.8 percent of the country's total population of 3.4 million have received two COVID-19 vaccine doses, while more than 1,026,700 have received a third dose. More than 107,400 Mongolians have received a fourth dose, which the country started to administer on Jan. 7 on a voluntary basis.  â– 